      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 25
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the refined 3.6L M96.03 flat-six power plant. This high-revving boxer engine exhibits excellent compression across all cylinders and has had the IMS bearing proactively replaced with a dual-row ceramic upgrade. Power is routed through a G96 6-speed manual transaxle with a crisp short-throw shifter and a recently serviced clutch assembly. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry with updated Bilstein B6 dampers for improved rebound control. Braking performance is anchored by four-piston Brembo monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing minimal lip wear. While the exterior shows minor road-rash and typical patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the mechanical vitals\u2014including the Rear Main Seal and AOS\u2014are in excellent order. This is a communicative, analog driving machine for the purist.",
      "price": 32500.0,
